{
  "local_port": 46026,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some free alternatives to Aha.io?",
  "response": "There are several free alternatives to Aha.io that offer project management, roadmapping, and collaboration features. While they may not have all the advanced functionalities of Aha.io, they can still be effective for managing projects and roadmaps. Here are some popular free options:\n\n### **1. Trello**\n   - **Overview**: Trello uses a Kanban-style board to manage tasks and projects.\n   - **Key Features**: Drag-and-drop task management, customizable boards, checklists, and collaboration tools.\n   - **Free Plan**: Unlimited boards, cards, and members with some limitations on power-ups and integrations.\n\n### **2. Asana**\n   - **Overview**: A versatile project management tool for task tracking and team collaboration.\n   - **Key Features**: Task lists, timelines, boards, calendars, and integrations with other tools.\n   - **Free Plan**: Supports up to 15 team members with basic task and project management features.\n\n### **3. ClickUp**\n   - **Overview**: An all-in-one productivity platform with features for task management, goal tracking, and more.\n   - **Key Features**: Customizable views (list, board, calendar), time tracking, Gantt charts, and docs.\n   - **Free Plan**: Unlimited tasks and members with some feature limitations.\n\n### **4. Productboard**\n   - **Overview**: A product management tool focused on prioritizing features and customer feedback.\n   - **Key Features**: Roadmapping, user feedback tracking, and prioritization tools.\n   - **Free Plan**: Limited to 1 workspace and 1 board, suitable for small teams or individual use.\n\n### **5. Monday.com**\n   - **Overview**: A flexible work management tool for tracking projects, workflows, and teams.\n   - **Key Features**: Customizable workflows, timelines, automation, and integrations.\n   - **Free Plan**: Supports up to 2 users with basic project management features.\n\n### **6. Wrike**\n   - **Overview**: A project management tool with features for task management, collaboration, and reporting.\n   - **Key Features**: Gantt charts, task dependencies, time tracking, and real-time collaboration.\n   - **Free Plan**: Unlimited users but limited to 2 GB of storage and basic task management features.\n\n### **7. Airtable**\n   - **Overview**: A hybrid of a spreadsheet and a database, ideal for organizing and tracking projects.\n   - **Key Features**: Customizable views (grid, calendar, Kanban), collaboration tools, and integrations.\n   - **Free Plan**: Includes 1,000 records per base and 1 GB of public attachments.\n\n### **8. Notion**\n   - **Overview**: An all-in-one workspace for notes, databases, and project management.\n   - **Key Features**: Customizable pages, task management, collaboration, and templates.\n   - **Free Plan**: Unlimited pages and blocks with some limitations on file uploads and collaborators.\n\n### **9. GitLab (for Software Development Teams)**\n   - **Overview**: A DevOps platform that includes project management and roadmapping tools.\n   - **Key Features**: Issue tracking, roadmaps, CI/CD pipelines, and version control.\n   - **Free Plan**: Unlimited public and private repositories with basic project management features.\n\n### **10. OpenProject**\n   - **Overview**: An open-source project management tool for teams.\n   - **Key Features**: Gantt charts, task management, time tracking, and collaboration tools.\n   - **Free Plan**: Community edition is free but requires self-hosting.\n\n### **11. Freedcamp**\n   - **Overview**: A project management tool designed for small teams and freelancers.\n   - **Key Features**: Task management, calendars, file storage, and time tracking.\n   - **Free Plan**: Unlimited projects and users with some feature limitations.\n\n### **12. Zoho Projects**\n   - **Overview**: A project management tool with features for planning, tracking, and collaboration.\n   - **Key Features**: Gantt charts, task dependencies, time tracking, and issue tracking.\n   - **Free Plan**: Supports up to 3 users and 2 projects.\n\n### **13. Jira (Free for Small Teams)**\n   - **Overview**: A popular tool for software development teams, especially for Agile workflows.\n   - **Key Features**: Scrum and Kanban boards, issue tracking, roadmaps, and reporting.\n   - **Free Plan**: Supports up to 10 users with basic Agile and project management features.\n\n### **14. MeisterTask**\n   - **Overview**: A Kanban-based project management tool with a focus on simplicity and collaboration.\n   - **Key Features**: Customizable boards, task management, automation, and integrations.\n   - **Free Plan**: Unlimited projects and tasks with some feature limitations.\n\n### **15. Taiga**\n   - **Overview**: An open-source project management platform for Agile teams.\n   - **Key Features**: Scrum and Kanban boards, task tracking, and reporting.\n   - **Free Plan**: Community edition is free but requires self-hosting.\n\nThese tools offer a range of features that can help teams manage projects, track progress, and collaborate effectively without the cost of premium tools like Aha.io. The best choice depends on your team\u2019s specific needs, such as the size of your team, the complexity of your projects, and the features you require.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
